HEADWORD: Orbation
<hw>Or*ba"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>orbatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being orbate, or deprived
of parents or children; privation, in general; bereavement.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

